The auxiliary polynomial is

\begin{align*}r^{2} - 2r + 2\end{align*}

Solving for $r$ when the above is set to 0 yields

\begin{align*}r = \frac{-(-2) \pm \sqrt{(-2)^{2} - 4(1)(2)}}{2} = \frac{2 \pm \sqrt{4-8}}{2} = 1 \pm i\end{align*}

where $i = \sqrt{-1}$. Thus, the general solution is

\begin{align*}\displaystyle y = e^{x}(C\cos(x) + D\sin(x))\end{align*}
